cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new architecture for implementing an efficient unitary neural network and tests its performance on various tasks. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on using unitary matrices in artificial neural networks, particularly in recurrent neural networks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new architecture for neural networks and tests its performance on various tasks, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper tests the performance of the proposed architecture on the pixel-permuted MNIST digit recognition benchmark, which is a computer vision task. 
5. cs.SD (Sound): The paper tests the performance of the proposed architecture on the Speech Prediction Test (TIMIT), which involves sound data.
